                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 20: Agriculture and industry saw a decline in the growth of bank credit, while personal loans saw an upsurge on the back of robust home advances in 2008-09, the Reserve Bank of India said today. The growth in bank credit to agriculture in 2008-09 fell to 12.9 per cent from 19.1 per cent a year ago, while that to industry fell to 22.2 per cent from 25.2 per cent in 2007-08.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 20: Ranbaxy Laboratories today said Arun Sawhney had taken over as the managing director of the company, replacing Atul Sobti, who resigned on August 12. Sawhney, who was earlier president of the global pharmaceutical business of the company, has been appointed MD for three years.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 20: Industrialist Naveen Jindal-led Jindal Steel and Power Ltd (JSPL) has resumed work on its $2.1-billion project in Bolivia after the South American country allocated about 3,000 acres for the venture. The company has resumed activities to develop the El Mutun iron ore deposit and steel plant project in Bolivias Santa Cruz area, the leading steel maker said.                                                                                                                          
